headline: Mooove Over, Magnificent Seven. It’s Time to Invest in COW.
summary: A UBS analyst has come up with a new acronym for the most attractive part of the retail sector: COW.  It stands for Costco Wholesale, O’Reilly Automotive, and Walmart.  Periods of disruption—like the current environment’s roller-coaster tariff policy and uncertain economic outlook—allow these retailers to emerge stronger than peers, and each has its own specific competitive advantages.
